Sitting here in Jacksonville (where I did my first show as a rapper) with the first black female principal of Ed White highschool! It’s a blessing to be back! God is good! 🙌🏽

Resources and Money are gifts from God! Never work for them! Work to expand your purpose and you will never run out of either! God provides! He gives money and resources to fulfill His purpose on the earth in and through our lives. I have nothing! I own nothing! Everything is the Lord’s! This mindset has allowed me to see and experience things that I never dreamed were possible before my understanding expanded! 
.
.
.
#Faith #Think #GrowRich #bearfruit

A sincere moment of worship 10 years ago is blessing, encouraging and edifying me today. Young reece is ministering to me 💪🏾🥹. God loves you and you are never alone! Let this minister to you. Stop what you’re doing for a moment and let the Holy Spirit love on you!

Young people want God! They are searching for God just like everybody and the Gospel has power no matter your age! All they need is the gospel to be preached to them and they will respond! I see it every week! I hear the testimonies of parents who witness how the Holy Spirit changes their children from the inside out! They’re character, they’re conduct, they’re grades, and even they’re attitudes change when God shows up! When I Tell you God is Moving in young People In Jacksonville FL!!!! Bring your children to @tphjax and watch God move in there lives! I’m grateful for the opportunity to serve Jacksonville under the leadership of  @bishopmclaughlin 🙌🏽🙌🏽. Continue to pray for our young people! The world will know soon what God is doing in lil ol Jacksonville, FL!!!! 
.
.
.

Watching God work is exciting! We just have to get out of God’s way. Here are a few tips to help you out;
.
.
.
1. Say yes to God as fast as you can (the faster the better)
.
2. Show up with an expectation that something crazy and even mind blowing is gonna happen…. Nothing is guaranteed but a positive outlook usually produces more than a negative outlook.
.
.
3. Be honest with God because he already knows every pain, hurt, frustration, concern or deficiencies that you bring to the table.
.
4. God love you and everybody else because he made us all in his image!
.
.
5. Leave everything you think you know about God at the door when you walk in…. Miracles do happen more often than you think. So show up like God can teach you something new about hog infinite his power is.
.
.
#cometochurch #gotochurch #overflow #anointed #ilove #instagram #iloveeverybody

In my many years of experience I have learned a few things. Here are 3 that I would like to share:
.
.
.
1. Find someone who’s relationship with God inspires you and learn everything you can from them
.
.
2. Trust the process that God is using to develop you into a greater version of yourself. Keep showing up even when it gets uncomfortable.
.
.
3. Followership is just as equally important as leadership. It’s hard to be a leader if you’ve never followed anyone! 
.
.
#Follow #Leadership #Instagram

This truly a glorious day! 😂😂😂😂My dog beaux was the only one in my house that I never saw pray, read the word or show any interest in the gospel! This is a day that I’ve prayed 🤣😂. As for me and my entire house…… Glory 😂😂😂

I used to think I found God when I was 19 years old…. the truth is now I realize that God found me… God found me in my mess and turned it into a message to show others that God’s love is real. Here are a few things I learned along the way; 
.
.
.
1. People rarely change. That’s why it’s important to love them where they are. God’s love is patient so we must be also.
.
.
2. There are people who will never agree with us. That’s ok. Everyone has the right to have another opinion. Never take it personal! 
.
.
3. Let God do the changing in people. If we change people with principles it won’t get them into heaven. 
.
.

#moreontheway #Lifeworks #livelife #Gospel #Churchmusic #goodadvice #godadvice
